column1: #Text=The Portland Trail Blazers ( 39 - 36 ) defeated the Sacramento Kings ( 29 - 45 ) 105 - 93 on Tuesday at the Moda Center in Portland .
#Text=The Trail Blazers got off to a quick start in this one , out - scoring the Kings 32 - 32 right away in the first quarter .

#Text=The Kings were the superior shooters in this one , going 48 percent from the field and 48 percent from the three - point line , while the Kings went 42 percent from the floor and just 47 percent from deep .
#Text=The Trail Blazers 000 backcourt duo of Damian Lillard and CJ McCollum were the bulk of the way for the Trail Blazers .
#Text=Lillard went 4 - for - 9 from the field and 3 - for - 5 from the three - point line to score a game - high of 13 points , while also adding nine assists in 29 minutes .
